body:
I was able to use 2018 version without any problem for Flutter development. After the 2019 update now intellisense is not working as expected.

It's suggesting everything by alphabetically instead of checking relations between parents/fields first then alphabetically.

[YouTrack Issue Page](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-209983).

May be we need some fix on Flutter plugin too.

## Version info

Intellij 2019.1 & Intellij 2019.1 + JBR 11
MacOS Mojave & Ubuntu 18.10 & Solus 4 (I test it on couple of Linux distros and two different macs)
Flutter 1.2.1
Latest Flutter and Dart Plugins

I just got two new screenshots @pq This guy is the popular one form YouTrack: :) This is another simple example. I scrolled down a bit for demonstrate the alphabetical ordering problem. With the "AboutDialog" widget, it's all alphabetical down below. By the way forgot to say, it firstly shows the suggestions from Dart itself.

'flutter doctor' seems to be from one computer but screenshots - from another. @softronaut am I right?
- I guess the problem on the first screenshot is that items like `ThemeData.xxx()` are not at the top of the completion list (or maybe not in the list at all?)
- As for the second screenshot, I don't see any problem. I think it has always been the same.

> 'flutter doctor' seems to be from one computer but screenshots - from another. @softronaut am I right? > > * I guess the problem on the first screenshot is that items like `ThemeData.xxx()` are not at the top of the completion list (or maybe not in the list at all?) > * As for the second screenshot, I don't see any problem. I think it has always been the same. @alexander-doroshko same computer. I launched Intellij for demonstrating the problem but I was using Android Studio while creating flutter doctor log, I think that's why you thought it was different computer. - Yes, I just realized it's not even available in the list and this is just an example, every widget have same problem. - Same project, almost same scroll level in Android Studio:

`flutter doctor` should list all IDEs, it doesn't care if it is launched or not. Ok, nevermind.

I guess, missing items like `ThemeData.xxx()` at the top of the completion list after `darkTheme:` is a question for @scheglov
As for the 2nd screenshot, I see a problem with the `Widget` item. It appears 3 times in the list (with different package info) but in fact, it's the same `Widget` class. //cc @scheglov for ideas.

1. Suggesting constructors (is this the problem with `ThemeData.xxx()`?) was implemented / restored in https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/9b77e4c507f28b730599b6386ddde989a0ad93dd
2. Showing `Widget` 3 times with different potential imports was thought as a feature - you can choose how to import. The library that is already imported is on the top. It might also be possible to refine this some more, for example do suggest other libraries when the class is already available in an already imported library. But I have not thought yet implications for amounts of data to transfer and computation to do. I will need to make an experiment at some point.

I was able to fix the problem by moving to the beta channel. You can do so by

```
flutter channel beta
flutter update --force
```
